@page "/"

<PageTitle>Home - DBC Parser</PageTitle>

<div class="jumbotron bg-light p-5 rounded-lg m-3">
    <div class="container">
        <h1 class="display-4">DBC File Parser</h1>
        <p class="lead">Upload and parse DBC (Database CAN) files to extract network information, messages, and signals used in automotive applications.</p>
        <hr class="my-4">
        <p>This application allows you to:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Upload DBC files for parsing</li>
            <li>View network structures with messages and signals</li>
            <li>Search through parsed data</li>
            <li>Extract automotive CAN bus information</li>
        </ul>
        <a class="btn btn-primary btn-lg" href="/dbc-upload" role="button">
            <span class="oi oi-cloud-upload" aria-hidden="true"></span> Upload DBC File
        </a>
    </div>
</div>

<div class="container">
    <div class="row">
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">What is DBC?</h5>
                    <p class="card-text">DBC (Database CAN) files are standard files used in the automotive industry to describe CAN bus networks, including messages and signals.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">Fast Processing</h5>
                    <p class="card-text">Our parser is designed to handle large volumes of DBC files efficiently, supporting server-side processing of 1000+ files per minute.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
        <div class="col-md-4">
            <div class="card">
                <div class="card-body">
                    <h5 class="card-title">Easy to Use</h5>
                    <p class="card-text">Simple web interface for uploading files and viewing parsed network information with messages and signals.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>
</div>
